Package yizhong.ding.mavendependencydownloader

Class Artifact

java.lang.Object
yizhong.ding.mavendependencydownloader.Artifact
public class Artifact extends Object
The Artifact class represents the logical artifact coordinates of maven artifact. It contains the coordinates (groupId, artifactId, and version) of an artifact.
Author:
Yizhong Ding

    • equals

      public boolean equals(Object o)
      Equals method compares the value of two Artifacts. Note: The override equals method only checks if values of groupId and artifactId of two Artifacts are equal. Motivation: Maven does not pull the same artifact twice. If already collected (in a different version) it should be considered covered, and not get re-downloaded.
      Overrides:
      equals in class Object

    • isSame

      public boolean isSame(Artifact target)
      This method compares if the value of two Artifacts are exactly same. This provides a more advanced comparison than the equals method, since this method also checks the artifact version (usually not a criteria for artifact comparison).
      Parameters:
      target - target artifact to compare with.
      Returns:
      true if they are same artifacts.
